<TITLE> Robbers shoot 3 in Bagerhat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bagerhat, August 15 (bdnews24.com)Three men received gunshot wounds when they attempted to stop a gang making their escape after a robbery in the village of Fatehpur in Bagerhat on Friday night. Fifty-year-old Gourapad Pal, 22-year-old Daud Sheikh and 25-year-old Jinnat Mina were admitted to Bagerhat Sadar Hospital with bullet injuries before being transferred to Khulna Medical College Hospital for further treatment. "A group of 10 to 12 armed robbers broke into the houses of Joynal Sheikh and Malek Mina at around midnight. Three locals were shot when they tried to block the gang's getaway," Monwar Hossain Tagar, former chairman of Bemorta union, told bdnews24.com. Ahammad Ali Molla, sub-inspector of Bagerhat Sadar Police Station, said a 29-year-old man had been arrested in connection with the incident. A case was yet to be filed, he said. bdnews
